============================================================
📱 BeReal Clone – Android Kotlin Portfolio Project (5 Weeks)
============================================================

🛠 Stack:
- Language: Kotlin
- Architecture: MVVM (or Clean Architecture)
- Backend: Firebase (Auth, Firestore, Storage)
- Camera: CameraX
- Notification: WorkManager or AlarmManager

============================================================
WEEK 1 – Planning & Setup
============================================================

[ ] Define MVP Scope:
    - Daily dual-camera photo
    - Timeline/feed
    - Login/signup
    - Friends system (basic)
    - Post visibility after submit

[ ] Sketch wireframes (paper or Figma):
    - Login screen
    - Camera screen
    - Feed/timeline
    - Profile

[ ] Initialize Android Studio Project:
    - Use Kotlin
    - Add Jetpack libraries: Navigation, ViewModel, LiveData

[ ] Setup GitHub repo:
    - Initial commit
    - Branching strategy (e.g., `main` + `dev`)

[ ] Setup Firebase:
    - Firebase Auth (email/password)
    - Firebase Firestore (user & post metadata)
    - Firebase Storage (for image uploads)

[ ] Create basic screens:
    - Splash screen
    - Login/signup screen (Firebase Auth)
    - Home/Feed placeholder

============================================================
WEEK 2 – Camera + Daily Notification
============================================================

[ ] Implement CameraX:
    - Request camera permissions
    - Capture photo with both front and back camera (sequentially is fine)
    - Show photo preview before upload

[ ] Create Camera Screen:
    - Front + Back camera trigger
    - Timestamp display
    - “Submit” button

[ ] Store photo to Firebase Storage:
    - Filename: userID_timestamp.jpg
    - Save front/back image separately or merged

[ ] Save post metadata to Firestore:
    - Fields: userId, timestamp, latePost (bool), photoURL

[ ] Add notification system:
    - Use WorkManager or AlarmManager to trigger daily prompt
    - Randomized time (optional) or fixed (e.g., 8 PM)

============================================================
WEEK 3 – Feed & Post Display
============================================================

[ ] Timeline UI:
    - Use RecyclerView to show friend posts
    - Post = username + photo + time + late flag

[ ] Fetch posts from Firestore:
    - Only show todays posts (filter by date)
    - Sort by time (newest first)

[ ] Allow users to post only once per day:
    - Check if user has posted today before showing camera

[ ] Handle late posts:
    - Compare user’s post time to notification time
    - Show “LATE” indicator if applicable

[ ] Profile Screen:
    - Show user info
    - Display personal post history

============================================================
WEEK 4 – Friends System & Polish
============================================================

[ ] Friend System (simplified):
    - Search friend by username
    - Send/accept friend request
    - Store friend list under each user (Firestore subcollection)

[ ] Feed filter:
    - Show only posts from friends
    - Optionally allow global view for demo

[ ] UI Improvements:
    - Add loading spinners and toasts
    - Handle errors (network, camera failure)

[ ] Add basic settings:
    - Logout
    - Username change

[ ] Add Firebase Analytics (optional)

============================================================
WEEK 5 – Testing, Polish & Portfolio Prep
============================================================

[ ] Test core flows:
    - Signup/login
    - Daily photo
    - Post visibility
    - Feed updates
    - Friend add/search

[ ] Polish UI:
    - Add icons, animations, or colors
    - Improve transitions and loading indicators

[ ] Offline support:
    - Show cached feed if offline
    - Queue post if upload fails (stretch)

[ ] Create README:
    - Include: overview, features, tech stack, screenshots, build instructions

[ ] Record demo video:
    - Use screen recorder + voiceover
    - Upload to YouTube or include in portfolio

[ ] Final cleanup:
    - Remove test users/posts
    - Push to GitHub
    - Shareable GitHub repo with README and link

